All-In Dragons — Auction System (FullProject)

## Overview
--------
This folder contains a small C++ CGI-based auction website used for class assignments.

- `index.cpp`         — Home page and login form
- `style.cpp`         — Dynamically generated CSS (built as `style.cgi`)
- `login.cpp`         — Login / registration / logout and session creation
- `listings.cpp`      — Listings of auctions (can be omitted for some submissions)
- `trade.cpp`         — Create auctions and place bids
- `transactions.cpp`  — Shows user transaction history
- `common.cpp`        — Shared helpers, DB credentials and session helpers

## Requirements
------------
- A Linux system with g++ (C++11), make
- MySQL server (or MariaDB) and the client development headers
- OpenSSL dev headers (the code uses SHA256 in `common.cpp`)
- Apache (or any CGI-capable web server) for production testing

Install dependencies
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install build-essential make g++ libmysqlclient-dev libssl-dev apache2
```

## Build (recommended)
-------------------
From inside this `FullProject` directory simply run:

```bash
make all
```
If you prefer manual compilation, these commands match the Makefile:

```bash
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o index.cgi index.cpp -lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o style.cgi style.cpp
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o login.cgi login.cpp -lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o listings.cgi listings.cpp -lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o trade.cgi trade.cpp -lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto
g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -o transactions.cgi transactions.cpp -lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto
chmod 755 *.cgi
```

Note: the `-lssl -lcrypto` flags are required when linking code that calls OpenSSL SHA256 functions.
If you see linker errors mentioning `DSO missing from command line` or undefined SHA256 symbols,
re-run the link with `-lssl -lcrypto` (or `make all MYSQL_LIBS='-lmysqlclient -lssl -lcrypto'`).

Database setup
--------------
The schema used by the application is in `schema.sql` (same directory).
-------------------------------

Troubleshooting
---------------
- Linker error 'DSO missing from command line' or undefined `SHA256`: add `-lssl -lcrypto` to your link flags.
- Missing header `mysql/mysql.h`: install the `libmysqlclient-dev` (or `mariadb-connector-c-devel`) package.
- Missing header `openssl/sha.h`: install `libssl-dev` (or `openssl-devel` on RHEL).
- If Apache shows 500 errors, check `/var/log/apache2/error.log` (or your distro's httpd log).
- SELinux systems may require `chcon -t httpd_sys_script_exec_t /var/www/html/cgi-bin/*.cgi` and booleans to allow DB connections.

